    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="991"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d991">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/235a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-21T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Refer to Department’s March 17, 10 p.m. There are no available arms at San
                    Antonio, but the War Department states that all arms and ammunition needed can
                    be shipped via New York and Vera Cruz at once, consigned military attaché, who
                    shall sell them only as directed by you. Price, Krag-Jorgensen carbines, War
                    Department’s preference, $6.40 gold; rifles, same make, $7.40 gold; and
                    ammunition $15 per thousand rounds. You will arrange for necessary permit for
                    entry of shipment, and inform Department quantity needed, and whether desired at
                    once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
